OL,3,CLabour MP with disabled son says he
OL,4,Cwon't vote for benefits changes
OL,6,FNorth Somerset's Labour MP has said he
OL,7,Fis prepared to vote against the
OL,8,Fgovernment on controversial changes to
OL,9,Fbenefits, which he believes would have
OL,10,Fa detrimental impact on his disabled
OL,11,Fson's future.
OL,13,FSadik Al-Hassan told ITV West Country:
OL,14,F"I don't think I could ever vote for
OL,15,Fsomething that would make his life in
OL,16,Fthe future worse, or other people like
OL,17,Fhim, and for me that's a red line."
