OL,3,CLabour MP with disabled son says he
OL,4,Cwon't vote for benefits changes
OL,6,FThe Labour MP is one of more than 120
OL,7,Fwho have signed an amendment that
OL,8,Fwould block cuts to disability and
OL,9,Fsickness-related benefits payments, in
OL,10,Fa government bid to save #5bn a year
OL,11,Fon the welfare bill by 2030.
OL,13,FIt's a rebellion significant enough in
OL,14,Fsize to wipe out Labour's majority in
OL,15,Fthe House of Commons, but Sir Keir
OL,16,FStarmer has doubled down on the plans
OL,17,Fand insisted he intends to "press
OL,18,Fahead" with next week's vote.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
