OL,3,CLabour MP with disabled son says he
OL,4,Cwon't vote for benefits changes
OL,6,FThe Labour MP was joined by the Forest
OL,7,Fof Dean's Matt Bishop and Stroud's Dr
OL,8,FSimon Opher in publicly expressing
OL,9,Fdiscomfort with the changes, while ITV
OL,10,FWest Country understands a number of
OL,11,Fother MPs in the West Country remain
OL,12,Fhesitant to back them.
OL,14,FAmong the most unpopular is a change
OL,15,Fto the way personal independence
OL,16,Fpayments (PIP) are granted, meaning
OL,17,Fpeople with less severe conditions are
OL,18,Fat risk of losing out on the benefit
OL,19,Fthat helps with the extra living costs
OL,20,Fof being disabled.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
