OL,3,CLabour MP with disabled son says he
OL,4,Cwon't vote for benefits changes
OL,6,F"For me, it's a personal choice
OL,7,Fbecause when I look at these proposals
OL,8,FI see them through the lens of a
OL,9,Ffather. But I think there are better
OL,10,Fways to raise revenue and better ways
OL,11,Fto intervene with regards to welfare."
OL,13,FHe added: "We do need to rebuild it
OL,14,F(the system), but we need to put the
OL,15,Fpeople in it, and helping them, at the
OL,16,Fheart of that. The bill misses the
OL,17,Fmark on that."
