OL,3,CLabour MP with disabled son says he
OL,4,Cwon't vote for benefits changes
OL,6,FA number of the proposed changes have
OL,7,Fbeen welcomed by Labour MPs, like
OL,8,Fextra investment to help get people
OL,9,Fback into work and an increase in the
OL,10,Fbasic rate of Universal Credit for
OL,11,Fpeople actively seeking employment.
OL,13,FBut MPs, like Al-Hassan, Bishop and
OL,14,FOpher, say there has been a lack of
OL,15,Fconsultation over the plans and an
OL,16,Finadequate impact assessment on the
OL,17,Fconsequences on the jobs market and on
OL,18,Fpeople's health.
